audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:34:| 2 | No complete executable v2 DGP | **NOT CLEARED** | V3 supplies an inventory and several equations, but not one coherent runnable model. `S_j` is a mean while `M_D` is an expanded sum; the MNAR estimator is mislabeled HT; `N`, reach membership, matched information, credit dependence, complete score/gate/oracle equations, format regime, and numerical conventions are missing. The proposed zero controls do not create symmetry (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:44-64,92-98`; `critique-v3-complete-dgp.md`). |
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:35:| 3 | Parity estimand not frozen; functional choice can flip sign | **PARTIAL** | One functional is genuinely chosen in prose: `E[(D-C)/O]`, estimated by the mean of per-world ratios (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:16-30`). But the displayed formula averages all worlds while the next rule conditions away `O<=o_min`; neither `o_min` nor `delta` is fixed or justified; sign, materiality, transport, and Monte Carlo states are conflated; and the only shipped gate still mixes three functionals (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:26-35,74-81`; `critique-v3-frozen-estimand.md`). |
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:36:| 4 | Invalid claim that the new model extends `beta=1-eta` | **CLEARED (narrowly)** | V3 explicitly retires the claim and correctly separates a limiting analytic benchmark from the numerical full frontier (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:83-90`). The replacement theorem is not ready: `a` cancels under fixed quota/no gate, the covariance ratio reaches the frozen ratio estimand only under a large-`K`, positive-oracle concentration argument, and the MNAR `beta` mapping is not elliptical in finite samples (`critique-v3-analytic-benchmark.md`). The old false claim is cleared; the new benchmark remains unfinished. |
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:37:| 5 | A joint law can choose every headline | **PARTIAL** | Making the full-parameter conditional frontier and set extrema primary removes probability-law weighting from the pointwise sign (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:100-106`). But the lower-dimensional `theta_surface` has no fixed-slice versus robust-projection rule, so an outer law could leak back through omitted coordinates. A bare admissible set cannot produce region mass, and the Shapley game, sampler, law family, and nested estimator are still unspecified (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:74-78,92-106`; `critique-v3-measure-free-sensitivity.md`). |
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:38:| 6 | Multiplier quarantine not mechanically enforceable | **NOT CLEARED** | Section 8 is a future engine specification, not a control in the repository (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:108-119`). The old engines remain directly runnable outside any legacy guard; E4 emits `D/C` and ASCII `x`; no schema/lint/snapshot/CI command exists. “Forbidden by default” also leaves a possible opt-in ratio path (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:31-36,108-113`; `critique-v3-mechanical-embargo.md`). |
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:39:| 7 | Novelty claim premature | **PARTIAL** | V3's conditional positioning is much more honest (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:121-125`), and no exact prior match was found for its full transport-set + signed-MNAR + proxy/credit combination. But budgeted noisy expert-versus-crowd portfolio selection, epistemic PB, noisy-PB robustness, and uncertainty-set project portfolios are already published. “Theorem-backed” and “pre-registered atlas” are not present-tense contributions while the proof, engine, `T`, and bridge data do not exist (`critique-v3-novelty-positioning.md`). |
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:41:**Clearance count: 1 cleared narrowly, 4 partial, 2 not cleared.**
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:43:## Remaining blockers, ranked
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:45:### 1. The observation model is not unit-consistent, and the central parameters are not identified
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:47:The primary truth is `S_j=mean_i(u_ij)`, but the distributed score is `sum(reports)/p`
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:48:(`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:47-50`). Even with `beta=0`, its conditional expectation is approximately `n_j S_j`, so
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:49:heterogeneous reach changes the distributed ranking while the central arm estimates a mean. With negative reports
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:50:included at probability `p(1-beta)`, dividing all reports by `p` intentionally leaves adverse-voice attenuation;
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:51:it is not a Horvitz–Thompson estimator of the true total or mean.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:53:The central model has a separate exact problem. If `Sbar_j` is the project-population mean already denoted by
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:54:`S_j`, then
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:56:```text
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:57:M_Cj = (a + w v_p) + (b - w) S_j + eta_j.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:58:```
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:60:With `v_p` fixed per run, infinitely many `(a,b,w)` triples generate identical signals. Eligibility, z-scoring,
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:61:and nonlinear selection cannot identify coefficients that are already observationally equivalent at the signal
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:62:level (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:51-57`; `critique-v3-complete-dgp.md`).
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:64:**Required fix:** choose mean or total value and put truth, both signals, delivery, and the oracle on that same
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:65:scale. Define project-specific planner own values `v_pj` and a distinct citizen target `mu_j`, with direct bridge
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:66:observations and rank conditions, or reparameterize to the identified composites and stop interpreting `a,b,w`
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:67:separately. Then specify reach, matched information, score, gate, hurdle, oracle, and format equations completely.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:69:### 2. The transport “identified set” is still an analyst-supplied placeholder
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:71:V3 requires a committed `T`, but supplies no endpoints, joint restrictions, coordinatewise nulls, amplification
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:72:treatment, provenance, or extracted source coefficient/covariance object (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:66-78`). The source
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:73:numbers are different estimands on different scales, and the diagonal multiplicative bridge is itself an
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:74:unjustified restriction (`E4-empirical-anchors.md:18-26,39-52,66-71`). A narrow and a very wide set can both include
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:75:zero and a sign reversal while producing opposite robust-sign maps.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:77:**Required fix:** freeze one machine-readable object
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:78:`S_source x R_scale x T x N_admissible`, including exact source estimands, sampling covariance, scale/link maps,
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:79:joint transport bounds, amplification/adverse cases, nuisance sets, and nested sensitivity sets. Project that set
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:80:through `m` without also treating transport-generated target coefficients as free axes. If the bounds are based on
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:81:assumption rather than target observables, call them **transport-sensitivity bounds conditional on `T`**, not an
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:82:empirically identified region.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:84:### 3. The mechanical embargo and replacement engine do not exist
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:86:The repository does not implement any of §8's controls. The ASCII/Unicode distinction is a concrete bypass: v3
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:87:says `×`, while the live E4 output uses `x` and also presents bare ratio values with parity at one
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:88:(`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:108-119`; `scripts/simulation/e4-v4-symmetric-frontier.mjs:73-104`). Moving a file alone would
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:89:not be enough if it remains directly executable or importable by the evidence path.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:91:**Required fix:** ship one evidence-only v3 command backed by a closed schema (`additionalProperties:false`) that
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:92:cannot contain `D/C` or ratio-parity semantics; render every official artifact through one tested adapter; reject
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:93:ASCII `x`, Unicode `×`, and bare `D/C`; and isolate old runners behind an explicit legacy-only runtime guard and
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:94:separate CI artifacts. Make unknown, unused, and non-allowlisted model literals fail.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:96:### 4. The estimand's domain and state machine are not frozen
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:98:The exclusion rule changes the displayed estimand to a conditional one, but the formula does not say so
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:99:(`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:22-30`). The transport classifier sends every interval that is not wholly material-central or
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:100:material-distributed to `transport-indeterminate`, including intervals wholly inside the negligible band and
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:101:intervals with an identified positive sign but uncertain materiality (`DESIGN_SKETCH_v3.md:31-35,74-81`). There is
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:102:also no `numerically-unresolved` state for Monte Carlo or optimization uncertainty.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:104:**Required fix:** define and co-report
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:105:`pi_deg(theta)=Pr(O<=o_min|theta)` and
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:106:`m_cond(theta)=E[(D-C)/O|theta,O>o_min]`; freeze exact, scale-aware `o_min` and `delta`; report sign status at zero
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:107:separately from materiality at `+/-delta`; add robust-negligible and numerical-certification fields; and distinguish
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:108:the family of fixed-transport frontiers from the projected parity-compatible set.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:110:### 5. The analytic benchmark and sensitivity/display contracts remain promises
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:112:The covariance-ratio lemma is valid under a common normal fixed-threshold model: expected selected value per
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:113:candidate is
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:115:```text
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:116:q*E[S] + phi(z_q) * Cov(S,X_k)/sd(X_k).
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:117:```
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:119:Parity therefore equates the two covariance ratios. But an exact top-`qK` portfolio is finite-sample order-statistic
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:120:selection, `a` cancels under no gate/fixed quota, and the frozen oracle-normalized mean requires `O_K/K` to
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:121:converge to a positive constant plus appropriate integrability (`critique-v3-analytic-benchmark.md`). The actual
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:122:MNAR signal has value- and `beta`-dependent sampling variance, not an exact elliptical law. Likewise, a plotted
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:123:`theta_surface` needs an explicit fixed-slice or worst-case projection operator before it is truly measure-free
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:124:(`critique-v3-measure-free-sensitivity.md`).
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:126:**Required fix:** state and prove a joint-normal fixed-threshold theorem plus a large-`K` positive-oracle limiting
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:127:corollary; derive the actual `beta` moments or label them a CLT approximation; remove `a` from the benchmark surface;
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:128:and freeze the display operator, all secondary law families, and any Shapley game before production output.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:130:## Prior-art result and positioning
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:132:The sharper search materially narrows the contribution:
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:134:- [Böttcher and Klingebiel, “Organizational Selection of Innovation”](https://doi.org/10.1287/orsc.2023.17357)
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:135:  already model budget-constrained true-quality portfolio selection under noisy expertise and compare expert
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:136:  delegation with collective aggregation, with either able to win.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:137:- [Rey and Endriss, “Epistemic Selection of Costly Alternatives”](https://doi.org/10.1007/s10458-024-09677-2)
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:138:  already treat citizen ballots as noisy signals of the ground-truth set of costly projects to fund.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:139:- [Boehmer et al., “Robustness of Participatory Budgeting Outcomes”](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2305.08125) already
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:140:  simulate heterogeneous-cost PB robustness to noisy votes and show rule/completion choices are load-bearing.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:141:- [Liesiö, Mild, and Salo, “Preference Programming for Robust Portfolio Modeling and Project Selection”](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ejor.2005.12.041)
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:142:  and successors already identify robust project/portfolio conclusions over uncertainty sets.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:143:- [Mollick and Nanda, “Wisdom or Madness?”](https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.2015.2207) already compare crowd and expert
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:144:  funding judgments on the same project proposals and examine downstream outcomes.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:146:No exact match was found in this targeted, non-exhaustive scan for the full combination of a source-to-target
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:147:transport set, signed MNAR coverage, proxy/credit separation, and oracle-normalized institutional parity bounds.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:148:That narrow synthesis may be useful. The honest present contribution is therefore a **proposed analytic benchmark +
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:149:transport-sensitivity atlas + bridge measurement protocol**. It becomes a standalone theory contribution only
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:150:with a nonstandard E4-specific theorem, and an empirical contribution only with target-domain bridge data.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:151:“Noisy expert versus crowd budgeted selection,” “sometimes the central wins,” and “robustness atlas” are not
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:152:themselves novel.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:154:The companion documents must also be aligned before preregistration. The foundation still calls systematic bias
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:155:the “novel force,” labels target ranges proxy-anchored, and says the new boundary extends the retired law
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:156:(`research/e4-value-estimation-foundation.md:18-35,48-63`). The empirical-anchor file likewise calls target `a,w`
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:157:proxy-anchored despite conceding unverified transport (`E4-empirical-anchors.md:57-71`). Those are live overclaim
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:158:paths even if v3 itself is worded carefully.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:160:## Single sharpest improvement
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:162:**Replace the prose-only §3/§4/§8 stack with one unit-consistent, machine-readable model contract that generates
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:163:the registry, engine configuration, transport set, result schema, and tests.** Before generating it, choose mean
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:164:or total value and either identify `v_pj,mu_j,a,b,w` from distinct project-level bridge variables or use only the
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:165:identified composites. This one contract would expose every hidden law and literal, prevent the mean/sum error,
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:166:make exact symmetry testable, define the object optimized over `T`, and give the output embargo something real to
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:167:enforce.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:169:## Multiplier-relapse risk
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:171:**YES — material.** The prose is substantially safer, but the repository reality is unchanged: the named E4
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:172:runner still leads with `D/C`, uses parity at one, and emits ASCII `x`; the old gate mixes estimands; the runners are
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:173:not behind a legacy guard; and there is no v3 schema/lint/snapshot/CI path (`scripts/simulation/e4-v4-symmetric-frontier.mjs:59-66,73-104`;
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:174:`scripts/simulation/e5-sp-symmetry-gate.mjs:21-23,102-113,140-155`; `package.json:6-8`). The risk becomes **NO** only
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:175:when a closed evidence schema prohibits ratio semantics, all official renderers consume only that schema, both
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md:176:ASCII and Unicode suffixes are tested, and legacy execution cannot feed v1.14 artifacts.
