1:# v1.14 / E4 design — v4 (supersedes v3) — one unit-consistent model contract
3:> Closes the v3 critique (`CRITIQUE_v3_SUMMARY.md`, `critique-v3-*.md`). v3's single sharpest fix was: **replace the
4:> prose §3/§4/§8 stack with ONE unit-consistent, machine-readable model contract** that generates the registry,
5:> engine config, transport set, result schema, and tests. v4 is that contract. It also integrates the author's
6:> **three-tier domains** (`THREE-TIER-VARIABLE-DOMAINS.md`) and adds a **capability criterion**: the design must be
7:> able to surface a strong, defensible result *if the mechanism is real* — neither gerrymandered to a null nor to a
8:> positive. Everything is on the **mean value scale**. NOT pre-registered — attack until clean.
10:---
11:## A. CAPABILITY CRITERION (new, first-class)
12:A design that can only ever return "indeterminate" is as dishonest as one tuned to a positive. So v4 is judged on
13:BOTH:
14:- **Not gerrymandered to a null:** the physically-possible set `D_F` excludes math-only artifacts (sign-reversal of
15:  a directional mechanism = "negative car speed"); indeterminacy must be *earned within D_F*, not imported from `D_M`.
16:- **Not gerrymandered to a positive:** the expectable set `R_α` must be a defensible evidence-concentrated band,
17:  pre-registered, with a coverage family (α∈{.5,.8,.95}); a Codex reviewer must be unable to widen/narrow it to
18:  flip the headline.
19:The **impressive-but-bulletproof** outcomes this admits: (i) a region where `m_lo>0` over ALL of `D_F` ("distributed
20:wins even at the edge of the possible, incl. zero transport"); (ii) the **theorem** with magnitude recovered at the
21:boundary; (iii) a conditional identified magnitude interval over `R_α` ("where expectable, +X–Y% true value").
23:---
24:## B. THE MODEL CONTRACT (unit-consistent; mean scale everywhere)
25:All value quantities are **per-interested-person means**. One scale, one interface for all three arms.
27:### B.1 Population, reach, projects
28:```
29:N                         total population (registered)
30:K                         number of candidate projects
31:q_j   ~ Normal(m_q, s_q²)        project quality (latent), sd s_q
32:r_j   ~ Beta(α_r, β_r)           reach fraction (interested share) of project j
33:I_ij  ~ Bernoulli(r_j)           person i interested in j    (independent across i)
34:n_j   = Σ_i I_ij                 interested count;  if n_j = 0 → project j inadmissible in ALL arms (dropped, logged)
35:c_j   ~ Uniform[c_lo, c_hi]      cost;   B = φ · Σ_j c_j       budget
36:```
37:Permitted dependencies (declared, default = independent): `(q_j, r_j, c_j)` may be coupled via a stated Gaussian
38:copula `Σ_dep` (off by default; `Σ_dep = I`).
40:### B.2 Individual value and the truth (mean scale)
41:```
42:u_ij  = q_j + ε_ij ,   ε_ij ~ Normal(0, σ²)          individual valuation of j (only defined for I_ij = 1)
43:S_j   = n_j⁻¹ Σ_{i: I_ij=1} u_ij                     TRUTH = interested-population mean value  (→ q_j as n_j→∞)
44:```
45:`S_j` is a **synthetic model score under the declared aggregation A = mean** (primary). Alternative `A`
46:(e.g. median, floor-weighted) are **separate normative estimands**, never randomized into one prior.
48:### B.3 Distributed estimate — baseline-expanded, MNAR-biased MEAN (not HT)
49:```
50:R_ij | I_ij=1 ~ Bernoulli( p )        if u_ij ≥ 0
51:              ~ Bernoulli( p(1−β) )    if u_ij < 0        (adverse voice bias β)
52:M^D_j = n_j⁻¹ Σ_{i:I_ij=1} R_ij (u_ij + e_ij) / p ,     e_ij ~ Normal(0, σ_e²)
53:```
54:**Conditional expectation (printed in the pre-registration):**
55:```
56:E[M^D_j | u_·j] = n_j⁻¹ ( Σ_{u_ij≥0} u_ij + (1−β) Σ_{u_ij<0} u_ij )   =  S_j − (β/n_j)Σ_{u_ij<0} u_ij .
57:```
58:So at β=0 it is exactly `S_j` (mean scale, reach-invariant); β is the identified adverse-voice bias, **not** an HT
59:weight. This is deliberately labeled the **behavioral coverage estimator**, not an unbiased estimator.
61:### B.4 Central estimate — identified via project-varying planner projection (the stadium fix)
62:The planner never observes `S_j`. The planner projects a value `v_{p,j}` onto j from **observable category priors**
63:(the "sports-facility ⇒ 80" prior), which is **wrong** where the true beneficiary population differs (chess users
64:⇒ `S_j`≈0). `v_{p,j}` varies across projects **independently of `S_j`** — this is what identifies the model:
65:```
66:M^C_j = a + b·S_j + w·(v_{p,j} − S_j) + η_j ,   η_j ~ Normal(0, σ_C²)
67:      = a + (b − w)·S_j + w·v_{p,j} + η_j .
68:```
69:- **Identification:** with regressors `S_j` and `v_{p,j}` of **full rank** (Cov(S,v_p) < sd·sd, guaranteed because
70:  `v_{p,j}` is the planner's category prior, a distinct object from realized `S_j`), `(b−w)`, `w`, and `a` are all
71:  identified. **Rank condition stated; where transported to reality, `v_{p,j}` = planner forecast and `S_j` = a
72:  bridge measurement must be jointly observed** (the bridge protocol; §G).
73:- **Generation of `v_{p,j}`:** `v_{p,j} = v_p0 + γ·g_j + ξ_j`, `g_j` = observable category signal (corr. ζ with
74:  `q_j`, `ζ<1`), `ξ_j ~ Normal(0, σ_v²)`; `v_p0` = planner's own baseline. (All in `θ_all`.)
75:- **Format regime (executable):** a toggle `fmt ∈ {point, dist}`; `a = a_res + fmt·a_fmt` where the point regime
76:  adds the reducible format bias `a_fmt` and the distribution regime removes it (D-L-S: distribution elicitation
77:  halves the bias). `a_fmt, a_res` are both in `θ_all`; `fmt` activates it, so no parameter is dead.
79:### B.5 One common selection interface (all three arms)
80:For arm `k ∈ {C, D, O}` with score signal `X^k_j` (`X^C=M^C`, `X^D=M^D`, `X^O=S` the oracle):
81:```
82:eligible:   E^k_j = 1{ X^k_j − h·c_j > 0 }                      opportunity-cost hurdle h (shared)
83:value rank: R^k_j = z_k( (X^k_j − h·c_j) / c_j )               z over the ELIGIBLE set, pop-sd, fallback sd→1
84:central credit tilt (C only): R^C_j ← (1−λ)·R^C_j + λ·z_C( P_j / c_j )
85:fund set:   greedy by R^k_j under budget B, exact residual-budget fill, tie-break by lower j (declared)
86:delivered:  D_W=Σ_{j∈fund^D} S_j ,  C_W=Σ_{j∈fund^C} S_j ,  O_W=Σ_{j∈fund^O} S_j     (gross, mean scale)
87:```
88:Credit law: `P_j = ρ_P·(visible salience of j) + noise`, salience from `(c_j, g_j)`, all declared in `θ_all`.
89:Every arm uses **its own** signal in its own gate (no oracle leakage); the oracle arm uses true `S_j`.
91:---
92:## C. THE FROZEN ESTIMAND + STATE MACHINE
93:Two co-reported functionals (both frozen), plus a degeneracy share:
94:```
95:π_deg(θ)  = Pr( O_W ≤ o_min | θ )                              degenerate-world share (reported, never hidden)
96:m(θ)      = E_W[ (D_W − C_W) / O_W | θ , O_W > o_min ]         THE estimand (conditional, per-world ratio mean)
97:```
98:`o_min` and `δ` are **frozen in mean-value units** (o_min = small positive fraction of median O; δ = a materiality
99:fraction justified in delivered-value terms, **not** the retired 0.05). Estimation: Monte-Carlo over worlds
100:(common random numbers across arms), world-cluster bootstrap CI covering **inner** (simulation) variability only.
102:**Classification state machine (per θ, over the transport/domain sets of §D):**
103:| state | condition |
104:|---|---|
105:| `robust-distributed` | `m_lo(θ) > +δ` |
106:| `robust-central` | `m_hi(θ) < −δ` |
107:| `robust-negligible` | `[m_lo, m_hi] ⊆ [−δ, +δ]` |
108:| `sign-robust-immaterial` | sign of `m` constant over the set but interval straddles ±δ (identified sign, uncertain size) |
109:| `transport-indeterminate` | sign of `m` flips **within `D_F`** |
110:| `numerically-unresolved` | MC/bootstrap/root-finder uncertainty exceeds the gap to the nearest boundary |
111:`π_deg` is always co-reported; a high-`π_deg` cell is flagged regardless of `m`.
113:---
114:## D. THREE-TIER DOMAINS replace the single transport set (author's contribution + Codex's machine-readable set)
115:Per transported/behavioral parameter, declare `R_α ⊆ D_F ⊆ D_M` (`THREE-TIER-VARIABLE-DOMAINS.md`). The frozen,
116:machine-readable transport object is:
117:```
118:Θ_transport = { S_source , R_scale , D_F , R_α(α) }
119:  S_source   exact source estimands + sampling covariance (B-S, G-B, D-L-S; different scales — declared)
120:  R_scale    scale/link maps source-units → model-units (stated, not diagonal-by-default; justified)
121:  D_F        physically-possible set per coeff (w≥0, b∈[0,b_max], g∈[0,g_max], β,p∈[0,1], σ≥0)   ← sign backbone
122:  R_α(α)     expectable band concentrating mass α, pre-registered, coverage family α∈{.5,.8,.95}  ← magnitude
123:```
124:Reports (three nested):
125:1. **Sign, over `D_F`, measure-free:** `m_lo=min_{D_F} m`, `m_hi=max_{D_F} m` → the state machine. Incorruptible.
126:2. **Magnitude, over `R_α`, measure-based (pre-registered):** identified interval `[m_lo^{R_α}, m_hi^{R_α}]` — the
127:   headline where expectable. Conditional-on-measure, labeled as such.
128:3. **`D_M \ D_F` — EXCLUDED with written justification** (sign-reversal etc.; the negative-speed analog).
129:**Honesty label (Codex-required):** because bounds rest on assumption, not target observables, they are
130:**"transport-sensitivity bounds conditional on the declared sets,"** NOT an empirically identified region.
132:---
133:## E. ANALYTIC BENCHMARK (joint-normal fixed-threshold) + numerical full frontier
134:**Theorem (to state + prove + regression-test).** Assume iid `(S, X_C, X_D)` jointly normal, equal costs, no gate,
135:no credit, common funded share `q`, threshold selection. With `z_q=Φ⁻¹(1−q)`:
136:```
137:V_k = q·μ_S + φ(z_q)·Cov(S,X_k)/sd(X_k)            expected delivered value per candidate (arm k)
138:V_D = V_C  ⇔  Cov(S,X_D)/sd(X_D) = Cov(S,X_C)/sd(X_C)      PARITY (the μ_S and φ(z_q) terms cancel)
139:```
140:with, for the central signal `X_C = a+(b−w)S+w·v_p+η` and `Z=v_{p}−S̄` typed as a **distinct** variable,
141:```
142:Q_C = Cov(S,X_C)/sd(X_C) = [b·Var(S)+w·Cov(S,Z)] / sqrt[b²Var(S)+w²Var(Z)+2bw·Cov(S,Z)+Var(η)].
143:```
144:**`a` is absent from the benchmark frontier** (intercept is rank-invariant under no-gate/fixed-share) — it operates
145:only in the numerical model (own-estimate gate + heterogeneous `/c_j`). **Large-K corollary** connecting to the
146:frozen estimand: if `O_K/K → V_O > 0`, `Pr(O_K≤o_min)→0`, and `(D_K−C_K)/O_K` is uniformly integrable, then
147:`m_K → (V_D−V_C)/V_O`; so parity (2) is the boundary **in the large-project limit** — finite-world `m` is numerical.
148:**β is not a slope:** under the report rule, `E[X_D|u]=U−(1−β)V` (U,V = pos/neg partial sums); its covariance/variance
149:follow the MNAR moments (Bernoulli-thinned, value-dependent variance) — stated as a **CLT/reduced-form
150:approximation**, never as `κ_D=1−β`. The numerical frontier (eligibility, heterogeneous costs, greedy fill, MNAR,
151:z-scoring, credit) is the object; the theorem is the limiting sanity check.
153:---
154:## F. FRESH ENGINE + CLOSED OUTPUT SCHEMA + MECHANICAL EMBARGO
155:- **One evidence-only command** (`npm run e4:evidence`) backed by a **closed JSON schema** (`additionalProperties:
156:  false`) whose fields are only: `{theta, pi_deg, m_hat, ci, m_lo_DF, m_hi_DF, m_lo_Ralpha, m_hi_Ralpha, state}`.
157:  The schema **cannot** express `D/C`, a ratio-with-parity-1, or any `×`/`x` suffix.
158:- **Every official artifact renders through one tested adapter** that rejects ASCII `x`, Unicode `×`, and bare
159:  `D/C` tokens in institution-performance context (lint test with both code points).
160:- **Legacy isolation:** `e4-v4-symmetric-frontier.mjs` and `e5-sp-symmetry-gate.mjs` move behind a `legacy/`
161:  runtime guard (env-gated), emit to a separate artifact namespace, and **cannot feed v1.14 outputs**; they run
162:  only as explicit regression checks.
163:- **Fail-closed config:** the engine loads `θ_all` from the contract; **any unregistered literal or unused field
164:  throws** (kills the `WP.eta`-style dead parameter and hidden constants).
165:- **Three test families (replace the "three-zero" slogan):**
166:  1. *Signal recovery:* `a=w=0,b=1,σ_C=0 ⇒ M^C=S`; `p=1,β=0,σ_e=0 ⇒ M^D=S`.
167:  2. *Exact joint symmetry:* feed both arms the identical realized signal/gate/score/budget/tie-break ⇒ require
168:     `D_W=C_W` **world-by-world**, not merely `m≈0`.
169:  3. *Pathway inactivation (paired worlds):* `λ=0 ⇒ P` has no effect; `w=0 ⇒ v_p` has no effect; `fmt` off ⇒ format
170:     has no effect; `β=0 ⇒ report prob sign-invariant`. Then add one asymmetry at a time.
171:  A separate **routing benchmark** (different information allocation, bias-neutral) may have nonzero `m`; that is
172:  the coverage/allocation effect, **not** a failed symmetry test.
174:---
175:## G. BRIDGE MEASUREMENT PROTOCOL (what would move PROXY-INFORMED → identified)
176:The only honest way to shrink `R_α`/`D_F` to a target-identified region: jointly observe, per project, the planner
177:forecast `M^C_pj` (= `v_{p,j}` proxy), a citizen value-distribution sample (→ `S_j`, dispersion), and realized
178:category signal `g_j`. The **optional gamified app** ("rate it + guess others", Prelec instrument) is the only
179:in-scope instrument (convenience sample → existence + direction of the gap, not population magnitudes). No surveys,
180:field work, or purchased data (author constraint). Absent bridge data, results stay **transport-sensitivity**, and
181:we say so.
183:---
184:## H. POSITIONING (honest, present-tense only for what exists)
185:Present contribution: **a proposed joint-normal fixed-threshold parity theorem + a transport-sensitivity atlas +
186:a bridge-measurement protocol**, for noisy/biased proxy-vs-coverage **budgeted** selection with signed MNAR and a
187:credit channel. It is NOT "theorem-backed" until the proof + regression tests ship, and NOT an empirical estimate
188:without bridge data. Differentiate explicitly from prior art (all cited): Böttcher & Klingebiel 2024 (noisy
189:expert-vs-collective budgeted portfolio selection); Rey & Endriss 2024 (epistemic selection of costly
190:alternatives); Boehmer et al. 2023 (PB robustness to noisy votes); Liesiö, Mild & Salo 2007 (robust portfolio
191:project selection over uncertainty sets); Mollick & Nanda 2016 (crowd-vs-expert funding). Our narrow, not-yet-
192:matched synthesis = transport-set + signed-MNAR coverage + proxy/credit separation + oracle-normalized institutional
193:parity bounds. "Sometimes the central wins," "robustness atlas," and "noisy expert-vs-crowd" are **not** themselves
194:novel and are not claimed as such.
196:---
